The paper is about generating realistic 3D faces, which is a topic that falls under computer graphics and computer vision. The use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) is also mentioned, which is a popular technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves generating 3D shapes, which falls under cs.GR (Graphics). Additionally, the use of GANs involves training a model, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves generating data from different modalities, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
